{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox person | name = Kaitlyn Alexander | image = Fan Expo Canada 2015 - Kaitlyn (20875925073).jpg | image_size = | caption = Alexander in 2015 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|10|9}} | birth_place = [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], Canada | education = | occupation = Actor, writer, web series creator, YouTube personality | years_active = 2014–present }}
'''Kaitlyn Alexander''' (born October 9, 1992) is a Canadian actor, writer, [[web series]] creator and [[List of YouTubers|YouTube personality]], best known as LaFontaine in the popular [[LGBT]] web series ''[[Carmilla (series)|Carmilla]]'' (2014–2016).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thesisterverse.com/saraandallisontalktv/podcasts/podcast-24-interview-kaitlyn-alexander-lafontaine-carmilla/|title=Podcast 24: Interview with Kaitlyn Alexander (LaFontaine in Carmilla) – Sara & Allison Talk TV|website=Sara & Allison Talk TV|language=en-US|access-date=2016-04-25}}</ref> In 2016, their [[Kickstarter]] and [[Indiegogo]]-funded web series ''[[Couple-ish]]'' (2015–2017) was nominated for a [[Streamy Awards|Streamy Award]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.zimbio.com/pictures/tS7yHT1GbxI/Official+Streamy+Awards+Nominee+Reception/Ibs7ESChSCH/Kaitlyn+Alexander|title=Kaitlyn Alexander in Official Streamy Awards Nominee Reception at YouTube Space LA|newspaper=Zimbio|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref><ref name="6th Annual Nominees">{{Cite news|url=http://www.streamys.org/nominees-winners/6th-annual-nominees/|title=6th Annual Nominees|newspaper=The Streamy Awards|accessdate=2016-10-27}}</ref>
== Early life == Alexander grew up in [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]]. As a kid, Alexander was very shy and only got into acting because it was a mandatory course in high school. Through that, they discovered how confident they felt while acting.<ref name=BOBO>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boboacademy.com/blogs/news/80183811-elli-interviews-the-incomparable-and-amazing-kaitlyn-alexander |title=Elli interviews the incomparable and amazing Kaitlyn Alexander!|first=Elli |last=S. |date=November 30, 2015|work=Starry Mag|accessdate=May 8, 2016|via=}}</ref>
They attended [[University of Toronto Mississauga]], in conjunction with [[Sheridan College]], for Theatre and Drama Studies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://popwrapped.com/exclusive-interview-kaitlyn-alexander|title=Kaitlyn Alexander Talks Gender And How They Found A Home In YouTube|website=PopWrapped|language=en|access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref> They spent six months in Germany.
== Career == Alexander began their [[YouTube]] channel on June 15, 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/realisticallysaying|title=realisticallysaying|website=YouTube|access-date=2016-09-01}}</ref> Their videos began to gain traction in 2014, when they became well known for playing LaFontaine in the web series ''[[Carmilla (series)|Carmilla]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://starrymag.com/?p=5126|title=Interviews Interviews – TV. Kaitlyn Alexander – Carmilla.|date=January 6, 2015|work=Starry Mag|accessdate=May 8, 2016|via=}}</ref> In 2016, Alexander played Max in five episodes of ''Full Out''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.weareopen.tv/open-tv-originals/fullout|title=Full Out|work=We Are Open|accessdate=March 17, 2016|via=}}</ref> In the same year they starred in the music video ''Melete'' by Laurence Made Me Cry.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.afterellen.com/people/468177-kaitlyn-alexander-stars-laurence-made-crys-music-video-melete |title=Kaitlyn Alexander stars in Laurence Made Me Cry's music video for "Melete" |first=Bendix |last=Trish |date=January 5, 2016|work=After Ellen|accessdate=May 8, 2016|via=}}</ref>
In addition to working as an actor, Alexander is also a musician and a writer.<ref name=AE1>{{Cite news|url=http://www.afterellen.com/people/483349-announcing-celebrity-judges-lovewinscontest |title=Announcing the Celebrity Judges for our #LoveWinsContest |first=Bendix |last=Trish |date=April 14, 2016|work=After Ellen|accessdate=May 8, 2016|via=}}</ref> They are also the creator of the web series ''[[Couple-ish]]'', in which Alexander acts as a main character, writer, producer and theme song singer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.afterellen.com/general-news/459771-couple-ish-stars-non-binary-queer-characters-youll-fall-love |title="Couple-ish" stars non-binary & queer characters you'll fall in love with |first=Dana |last=Piccoli |date=October 28, 2015|work=After Ellen|accessdate=May 8, 2016|via=}}</ref> They play the lead role, Dee, who is [[Genderqueer|non-binary]], [[Pansexuality|pansexual]] and open to date all genders.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.afterellen.com/video/466465-five-reasons-watching-couple-ish |title=Five Reasons Watching Couple-ish |first=Dana |last=Piccoli |date=December 12, 2015|work=After Ellen|accessdate=May 8, 2016|via=}}</ref> The series was funded through a successful [[Kickstarter]] campaign, which raised over $29,000 [[Canadian dollar|CAD]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/couple-ish/couple-ish|title=Couple-ish|website=Kickstarter|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> In 2016, the series was nominated for a [[Streamy Awards|Streamy Award]] in the Best Indie category, but ultimately lost to ''Brooklyn Sound''.<ref name="6th Annual Nominees"/>
Another successful [[Indiegogo]] campaign was launched in November 2016 to fund a second season, with a fixed goal of $45,000 [[United States dollar|USD]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/couple-ish-season-2-film-canada#/|title=Couple-ish Season 2|website=Indiegogo|access-date=2016-11-22}}</ref> The second season premiered on April 29, 2017.<ref>{{Citation|last=Couple-ish|title=Couple-ish {{!}}{{!}} Season 2 Ep 1 {{!}}{{!}} "Interview Pt. 2"|date=2017-04-29|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Efjruw4JwG8|accessdate=2017-05-05}}</ref>
=== Other work === Alexander is also the co-host of the ''[[Orphan Black]]'' after-show podcast.<ref name="AE1" />
== Personal life == Alexander lives in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]. They identify as [[queer]] and [[non-binary]], and go by [[singular they]] pronouns.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.afterellen.com/general-news/459771-couple-ish-stars-non-binary-queer-characters-youll-fall-love|title='Couple-ish' Stars Non-Binary & Queer Characters You'll Fall in Love With|last=Piccoli|first=Dana|date=October 28, 2015|work=After Ellen|access-date=March 17, 2016|via=}}</ref> They have credited [[Carmilla (series)#Main characters|LaFontaine]], the non-binary ''Carmilla'' character which they play, with helping them discover and accept their own identity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTDKeqwMiPY&feature=youtu.be&t=90|title=We Wrapped Carmilla S3 (And I have feelings about it)}}</ref>
