Kid Cudi's earliest influences include [[alternative hip hop]] groups such as [[The Pharcyde]], [[A Tribe Called Quest]] and [[Bone Thugs-n-Harmony]].<ref name=Soul/><ref name="huffpost">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/cara-parks/kid-cudi-the-lonely-stone_b_295982.html|title=Kid Cudi: The Lonely Stoner Hits His Stride|author=|date=November 23, 2009|work=The Huffington Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LbFoLa_XhVY|title=Myspace's My Favorite Videos: Kid Cudi|author=|date=October 24, 2009|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> Cudi also cites rappers such as [[The Notorious B.I.G.]], [[Tupac]], [[Jay Z]], [[Snoop Dogg]], [[Run-DMC]], [[Kurtis Blow]], [[LL Cool J]], [[Salt-N-Pepa]], [[Queen Latifah]], [[Kid 'n Play]], [[N.W.A.]], [[Naughty By Nature]], [[Onyx (group)|Onyx]] and [[Public Enemy (music group)|Public Enemy]], as his hip hop influences while growing up.<ref name="hiphopdx.com"/> Cudi has also credited fellow Ohio native [[Camu Tao]], as an influence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2010/08/the-king-of-columbus-a-look-at-camu-taos-posthumous-king-of-hearts.html|title=Pop & Hiss|author=|date=|work=latimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hiphopdx.com/news/id.11330/title.camu-taos-posthumous-king-of-hearts-to-release-peers-praise|title=- HipHopDX|author=HipHopDX|date=May 25, 2010|work=HipHopDX}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/review-kid-cudis-speedin-bullet-2-heaven-news.19091.html|title=Review: Kid Cudi's "Speedin' Bullet 2 Heaven"|author=Maxwell Cavaseno|date=December 13, 2015|work=HotNewHipHop}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.villagevoice.com/music/download-camu-taos-elvis-costello-borrowing-be-a-big-girl-sotc-premiere-6649530|title=Download Camu Tao's Elvis Costello-Borrowing "Be a Big Girl" (SOTC Premiere)|author=Christopher Weingarten|date=August 10, 2010|work=Village Voice}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.villagevoice.com/music/camu-tao-gets-his-due-6428542|title=Camu Tao Gets His Due|author=Phillip Mlynar|date=August 18, 2010|work=Village Voice}}</ref> He has also been inspired by the sounds of [[The O'Jays]], [[Ratatat]], [[MGMT]] and [[The Postal Service]].<ref name="huffpost"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2009/08/kid-cudi|title=Kid Cudi|author=|date=August 3, 2009|work=Complex}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/i-m-h-o/a-look-at-kid-cudis-man-on-the-moon-cfd9bc0ffc99#.mapgxo7ru|title=A look at Kid Cudi’s ‘Man on The Moon’ — I. M. H. O.|author=Addison Todd|date=|work=Medium}}</ref> In 2010, he began experimenting with [[rock music]]; rock acts that inspired Cudi include the [[Electric Light Orchestra]], [[Jimi Hendrix]], [[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]], the [[Pixies]] and [[Pink Floyd]].<ref name="listeningsession"/><ref name="billboard">{{cite web|author=Chris Payne|title=Kid Cudi, Dot Da Genius Preview 'WZRD' Album in NYC|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/504442/kid-cudi-dot-da-genius-preview-wzrd-album-in-nyc|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=February 24, 2012|accessdate=February 26, 2012}}</ref>

=== Influence ===
Kid Cudi has gone on to influence and inspire several artists himself, such as [[rapper]]s Kanye West,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2013/04/a-history-of-kid-cudi-and-good-music/the-originators-of-style|title=Kanye West Calls Himself and Cudi The "Originators of The [''808s''] Style" - A Timeline of Kid Cudi on G.O.O.D. Music - Complex|author=Lauren Nostro|date=April 3, 2013|work=Complex}}</ref> [[Travis Scott (musician)|Travis Scott]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theboombox.com/25-travis-scott-facts/|title=25 Facts You Probably Didn’t Know About Travi$ Scott|author=|date=May 29, 2015|work=The Boombox}}</ref> [[Kendrick Lamar]],<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EphqeLMwPoI|title=Kendrick Lamar talks J Cole, XXL Freshmen, Kid Cudi, Human Music|author=|date=December 31, 2010|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> [[Schoolboy Q]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2012/08/watch-the-first-episode-of-kendrick-lamar-and-schoolboy-qs-under-the-influence-of-music-tour-vlog|title=Watch The First Episode Of Kendrick Lamar And ScHoolboy Q's "Under The Influence Of Music" Tour Vlog|author=Daniel Isenberg|date=August 14, 2012|work=Complex}}</ref> [[Chance the Rapper]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/we-dug-up-chance-the-rappers-pre-acid-rap-material|title=We Dug Up Chance the Rapper's Pre-'Acid Rap' Material|author=|date=|work=NOISEY}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pigeonsandplanes.com/2013/07/chance-the-rapper-answers-reddits-questions-about-childish-gambino-frank-ocean-and-kid-cudi/|title=Chance the Rapper Answers Reddit's Questions About Childish Gambino, Frank Ocean, and Kid Cudi|author=|date=July 31, 2013|work=Pigeons & Planes}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=chancetherapper|author=Chance The Rapper|number=242346541329821698|date=September 2, 2012|title=kid cudi fan}}</ref> [[Childish Gambino]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/childish-gambino-discusses-working-with-kid-cudi-video.21261.html|title=Childish Gambino Discusses Working With Kid Cudi|author=Nicolas James|date=November 3, 2013|work=HotNewHipHop}}</ref> [[Logic (rapper)|Logic]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/09/logic-breaks-down-under-pressure/influences|title=He wears his influences on his sleeve. - Logic Breaks Down 10 Things You Need to Know About "Under Pressure" - Complex|author=Insanul Ahmed|date=September 22, 2014|work=Complex}}</ref> [[ASAP Rocky]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/28/t-magazine/asap-rocky-sundance-dope-interview.html|title=A$AP Rocky on His Sundance Hit, Mourning A$AP Yams and Why He Rejects Those Tupac Comparisons|author=|date=January 28, 2015|work=The New York Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://emptylighthouse.com/kid-cudi-encourages-individuality-fk-fitting-1661813969|title=Kid Cudi Encourages Individuality: 'F**k Fitting In'|author=|date=|work=Empty Lighthouse Music & Arts Magazine}}</ref> [[ASAP Nast]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://grantland.com/features/rap-and-the-influence-of-other-genres/|title=It Might Blow Up, and It Will Go Pop|author=Sean Fennessey|date=|work=Grantland}}</ref> [[Allan Kingdom]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://greenlabel.com/sound/allan-kingdom-glass-up-closed-sessions/|title=Allan Kingdom: "Don't Sugarcoat Anything"|work=Green Label|first=Peter|last=Marrack|date=January 28, 2015|accessdate=January 15, 2016}}</ref> [[Raury]],<ref name="nobs"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://trytattle.com/88/raury?r=twitter|title=Raury: 'I Probably Would Have Ended My Life if it Wasn't for Kid Cudi'|author=Rohn, Jake|date=August 2016|accessdate=November 16, 2016|work=TryTattle.com}}</ref> [[Two-9|Key!]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uproxx.com/smokingsection/key-when-i-tried-to-write-for-cudi-ep/|title=Key! – ‘When I Tried To Write For Cudi’ EP|author=|date=|work=UPROXX}}</ref> [[Kevin Abstract]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pigeonsandplanes.com/music/2014/07/stream-kevin-abstracts-free-album-mtv1987 |title=Stream Kevin Abstract's Free Album "MTV1987" |publisher=PigeonsandPlanes |date=July 15, 2014 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2016/02/the-best-thing-kevin-abstract-ever-did-for-himself-was-run-away-from-home |title=The best thing Kevin Abstract ever did for himself was run away from home &#124; For The Win |website=Ftw.usatoday.com |date=February 3, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref> and [[Jaden Smith]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://notionmagazine.com/jaden-smith-pays-homage-to-kid-cudi-in-back-to-the-future-inspired-video-for-fallen/|title=Jaden Smith pays homage to Kid Cudi in Back to The Future inspired new video - Notion Magazine|date=December 5, 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/jaden-smith-puts-on-for-kid-cudi-in-new-video-for-fallen-news.25951.html|title=Jaden Smith Puts On For Kid Cudi In New Video "Fallen"|publisher=}}</ref> as well as singers [[Jhene Aiko]],<ref name="rap-up.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2012/08/21/rap-up-tv-jhene-aiko-talks-souled-out-debut-love-for-kid-cudi-and-tupac/ |title=Rap-Up TV: Jhené Aiko Talks 'Souled Out' Debut, Love for Kid Cudi and Tupac |publisher=Rap-Up.com |date=August 21, 2012 |accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref> [[Lissie]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clashmusic.com/news/listen-lissie-covers-kid-kudi|title=Listen: Lissie Covers Kid Cudi|author=|date=|work=Clash Magazine}}</ref> and [[Tinashe]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tinashenow.tumblr.com/post/18292548247|title=TINASHE|author=|date=|work=tumblr.com|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222113728/http://tinashenow.tumblr.com/post/18292548247|archivedate=December 22, 2015|df=}}</ref> among others. In a 2010 interview with ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', Kanye West called Cudi his "personal favorite artist in the world right now. His whole take on the game is just unfiltered, uncensored artistry."<ref>{{cite web|author=Mariel Concepcion |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/951795/kanye-west-discusses-kid-cudi-jay-z-for-president |title=Kanye West Discusses Kid Cudi, Jay-Z For President |publisher=Billboard |date=November 4, 2010 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref> In a 2015 article titled "KiD CuDi - A Forgotten Influence on Psychedelic Introspection in Hip-Hop", the author wrote "Cudi helped bring about a new era of electronic, psychedelic driven production. And his dark, drug-riddled approach to introspection has already taken hold in the up-and-comers in the hip-hop world."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tremr.com/charlie-wooley/kid-cudi-a-forgotten-founder-of-psychadelic-introspection-in-hip-hop|title=KiD CuDi - A Forgotten Influence on Psychedelic Introspection in Hip-Hop|author=|date=|work=Tremr}}</ref>

In 2016, Kanye West called Cudi "the most influential artist of the past 10 years".<ref>{{cite web|author=Jordan Runtagh |url=http://www.people.com/article/kid-cudi-kanye-west-end-feud |title=Kanye Ends Feud with Kid Cudi with Onstage Compliments |website=People.com |date=September 21, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2016/09/kanye-west-shouts-out-kid-cudi-most-influential-artist-past-10-years |title=Kanye West Shouts Out Kid Cudi, Calls Him the "Most Influential Artist of the Past 10 Years" |publisher=Complex |date= |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref> [[West Coast hip hop]] duo [[Audio Push]] also praised Cudi in 2016, saying "The thing I love about Cudi is he's unapologetically real. He birthed so much of, not even the new generation of artists, but a lot of [your] favorite artists wouldn't be [your] favorite artists if it wasn't for Cudi."<ref>{{cite web|last=Schwartz |first=Danny |url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/audio-push-speak-on-kid-cudis-twitter-shoutout-and-influence-news.24341.html |title=Audio Push Speak On Kid Cudi's Twitter Shoutout & Influence |website=Hotnewhiphop.com |date=September 26, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref> In November 2016, [[Atlanta]]-based rapper [[OG Maco]], who has cited Cudi as a major influence on several occasions,<ref name="nobs">{{cite web|url=http://www.360nobs.com/2015/08/how-fetty-wap-vince-staples-and-dej-loaf-got-voted-into-the-xxl-freshman-10-list/|title=How Fetty Wap, Vince Staples And Dej Loaf Got Voted Into The 'XXL Freshman 10 List'|author=|date=|work=360Nobs.com}}</ref> released an [[Extended play|EP]] titled ''For Scott'', as a tribute to Kid Cudi.<ref>{{cite web|last=Walker |first=Angus |url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/og-maco-for-scott-new-mixtape.116624.html |title=OG Maco - For Scott |website=Hotnewhiphop.com |date=November 17, 2016 |accessdate=December 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=James |first=Andy |url=http://djbooth.net/news/entry/2016-11-07-og-maco-for-scott-kid-cudi |title=OG Maco’s "For Scott" EP is a Tormented Tribute to Kid Cudi |publisher=DJBooth |date=November 17, 2016 |accessdate=December 22, 2016}}</ref> Publications such as [[HotNewHipHop]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Lyons |first=Patrick |url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/tracking-kid-cudis-influence-news.24130.html |title=Tracking Kid Cudi's Influence |website=Hotnewhiphop.com |date=September 17, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kid-cudis-man-on-the-moon-the-end-of-day-influenced-a-generation-news.47481.html|title=Kid Cudi's "Man On The Moon: The End Of Day" Influenced A Generation|publisher=}}</ref> DJBooth<ref>{{cite web|last=Bradley |first=Brent |url=http://djbooth.net/news/entry/2016-09-15-kid-cudi-impact-on-hip-hop |title=Remembering Kid Cudi’s Impact and Influence on Hip-Hop |publisher=DJBooth |date=September 15, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref> and ''[[IBTimes]]''<ref>{{cite web|author=Alex Garofalo |url=http://www.ibtimes.com/kanye-west-feuds-kid-cudi-6-reasons-why-scott-mescudi-actually-culture-2416739 |title=Kanye West Feuds With Kid Cudi: 6 Reasons Why Scott Mescudi Actually Is 'The Culture' |website=Ibtimes.com |date= |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref> have all noted Cudi's influence on contemporary hip hop, since his breakthrough in 2008.

==Other ventures==
[[File:Kidcudi (300dpi).jpg|thumb|right|Kid Cudi performing in San Francisco on July 24, 2009.]]
===Fashion===
In September 2009, Kid Cudi teamed up with Japanese clothing company [[A Bathing Ape|BAPE]], for a collaboration that saw Cudi's likeness featured on [[Printed T-shirt|graphic T-shirts]], with the Japanese label's mascot, Baby Milo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/style/2013/08/every-bape-collaboration/bape-kid-cudi |title=Kid Cudi - A History of BAPE Collaborations |publisher=Complex |date=December 14, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Kan |first=Eugene |url=http://hypebeast.com/2009/9/kid-cudi-x-a-bathing-ape-tee |title=Kid Cudi x A Bathing Ape Tee |publisher=Hypebeast |date=September 3, 2009 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref> As of 2014, he has had five [[t-shirt]] collaborations with BAPE.<ref name="jrpc">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zwiZ0tLyNLU</ref>

In February 2011, Kid Cudi announced a collaboration with [[Paris]]ian brand, Surface to Air. In the [[Autumn|fall]] of 2011, Kid Cudi released a [[leather jacket]] collection in collaboration with the fashion label. Taking cues from the modern [[biker jacket]], the "[[Thriller (song)|Thriller]]-inspired" lineup offered two men's styles — the Fire Jacket V1 and the Champs Jacket V2 — each made from 100% genuine [[leather]]. A red stitch treatment was applied to the shoulders and inner arms of the otherwise black jackets. Lending itself to the important details, the collection features black heavy-duty gunmetal zippers and hardware, as well as tonal metal snap buttons. A variety of diagonal and vertical pockets live on the front exterior shell of the jackets and the interior is fully lined for added comfort. Kid Cudi can be seen wearing the jackets in music videos such as "[[All of the Lights]] and "[[Mr. Rager]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/style/2011/02/kid-cudi-surface-to-air-leather-jackets |title=Kid Cudi x Surface to Air Leather Jackets |publisher=Complex |date=December 14, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Li |first=Arby |url=http://hypebeast.com/2016/9/10-non-music-kid-cudi-projects |title=10 Non-Music Kid Cudi Projects |publisher=Hypebeast |date=September 29, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref>

In August 2014, [[Giuseppe Zanotti]] designed an exclusive [[sneakers|sneaker]] inspired by Kid Cudi’s style. During one of Kid Cudi’s concerts, the designer was inspired by his great artistry, energy and vibes. They soon got in touch to share their personal vision of a sneaker embodying Kid Cudi’s style.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.highsnobiety.com/2014/08/18/giuseppe-zanotti-designs-a-futuristic-sneaker-inspired-by-kid-cudi/|title=Giuseppe Zanotti Designs a Futuristic Sneaker Inspired by Kid Cudi|author=|date=|work=Highsnobiety}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/1425513/kid-cudi-high-top-sneakers/|title=Kid Cudi Teams Up With Italian Designer Giuseppe Zanotti For High-Top Sneakers|author=|date=|work=The Inquisitr News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/kid-cudi-just-out-kanyed-kanye-with-his-new-giuseppe-zanotti-sneakers|title=Kid Cudi Just Out Kanye'd Kanye With His New Giuseppe Zanotti Sneakers|author=|date=|work=NOISEY}}</ref>

===Modeling===
In January 2015, [[Coach, Inc.]] announced Kid Cudi as the new face of their brand, along with actress [[Chloë Grace Moretz]], to front its Spring campaign.<ref>{{cite web|last=Raiss |first=Liz |url=http://www.thefader.com/2015/01/20/coach-taps-kid-cudi-for-their-spring-campaign |title=Crop Top Enthusiast Kid Cudi Is The New Face Of Coach |publisher=The Fader |date=January 20, 2015 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Richy Rosario |url=http://www.vibe.com/2015/01/kid-cudi-coach-dreamers-campaign/ |title=Kid Cudi Displays His Model Best For Coach’s Dreamers Campaign |website=Vibe.com |date=January 21, 2015 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
In a January 2013 interview, Cudi revealed that he had stopped smoking [[Cannabis (drug)|marijuana]] two years earlier, both for the sake of his child and due to frustration with constantly being associated with the drug and [[Stoner culture#Cannabis subculture|stoner culture]]. In that same interview, Cudi said that while he believes in God, he considers himself [[spiritual but not religious]].<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.complex.com/music/2013/01/kid-cudi-talks-quitting-weed-bossing-up-illuminati-rumors-and-motm-iii | title = Interview: Kid Cudi Talks Quitting Weed, Bossing Up, Illuminati Rumors, and "MOTM III" | author = Joe La Puma | date = January 17, 2013 | accessdate = August 2, 2013 | publisher = Complex }}</ref>

In a March 2013 interview, Kid Cudi talked about how his initial sudden and unexpected fame drove him to [[alcohol (drug)|alcohol]] and drugs: 
{{bquote |quote = "For me, I just got to this point, and especially up until recently, I gave up liquor, I don’t drink anymore, it’s been five and a half months I’ve been sober. The booze was a new thing for me, I didn’t realize I was an [[alcoholic]] all these years. I had a problem, I think with any addiction you have to be ready to make the choice, whether it’s [[cigarette]]s or anything. You have to just commit and you just have to stick with it. I stopped everything [[cold turkey]]. When I had my [[cocaine]] problem I stopped cold turkey, I didn’t go to [[Drug rehabilitation|rehab]]. I don’t believe in these things. Some people need the extra help, not me. I wasn’t a [[drug addict]] before this crap, I wasn’t doing cocaine, I wasn’t getting [[Alcohol intoxication|wasted]] every night because I didn’t want to be alone. I wasn’t this dark person before the madness, I was a whole other dude. I don’t even think I smoked weed as much ‘cause we couldn’t afford it... You just have to make the choice and decide the person you wanna be and stick with it. You get to a certain age where the people around you are not gonna be on that rollercoaster all day long ready for you to go up, ready for you to go down, and stick with you through all the madness. People want you to be one person and stick with it and I chose to be clean and be sober and get my life together. For myself, for my health, for my daughter, for my family."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefix.com/content/kid-cudi-reveals-how-he-beat-his-addictions|title=Kid Cudi Reveals How He Beat His Addictions|author=|date=|work=The Fix}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hiphopdx.com/news/id.27973/title.kid-cudi-i-couldnt-deal-with-fame|title=- HipHopDX|author=|date=March 19, 2014|work=HipHopDX}}</ref>}}

In a 2013 interview, Cudi revealed he had suffered an addiction to [[antidepressants|anti-depressant medication]], which had been prescribed to help him deal with an "[[emotional breakdown]]" following a failed relationship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywood.com/general/kid-cudi-honoured-for-work-with-mental-illness-charity-59558884/|title=Kid Cudi honoured for work with mental illness charity|author=|date=|work=Hollywood.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/therootdc/post/breaking-hip-hops-silence-kid-cudi-speaks-on-mental-health/2013/01/17/257828fe-60b0-11e2-9940-6fc488f3fecd_blog.html|title=Breaking hip-hop’s silence: Kid Cudi speaks on mental health|author=Rahiel Tesfamariam|date=January 17, 2013|work=Washington Post}}</ref> In a 2014 interview, Cudi spoke on his struggles with [[Major depressive disorder|depression]] and [[suicide]] throughout the years: "I’ve dealt with suicide for the past five years. There wasn’t a week or a day that didn’t go by where I was just like, ‘You know, I wanna check out.’ I know what that feels like, I know it comes from loneliness, I know it comes from not having self-worth, not loving yourself."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hiphopdx.com/news/id.27910/title.kid-cudi-says-he-wants-to-help-kids-not-feel-alone-and-stop-kids-from-committing-suicide|title=- HipHopDX|author=|date=March 15, 2014|work=HipHopDX}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.centrictv.com/entertainment/music/articles/2014/03/18/rapper-kid-cudi-admits-suicide-thoughts-why-men-are-at-risk.html|title=Rapper Kid Cudi Admits Suicidal Thoughts, Why Men Are At Risk|author=|date=|work=CentricTV}}</ref>

In October 2016, Cudi revealed on his [[Facebook]] page that he had checked himself into [[Psychiatric rehabilitation|rehabilitation]] for [[Major depressive disorder|depression]] and [[Suicidal person|suicidal urges]].<ref name="usatoday">{{cite web|last1=Mallenbaum|first1=Carly|title=Kid Cudi: 'I checked myself into rehab' for depression, suicidal urges|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2016/10/05/kid-cudi-facebook-rehab-depression-anxiety-suicidal-urges/91588300/|website=USA Today|accessdate=October 5, 2016}}</ref><ref name="billboard2">{{cite web|last1=Brandle|first1=Lars|title=Kid Cudi Checks Into Rehab: 'There's a Ragin' Violent Storm Inside of My Heart'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7533351/kid-cudi-checks-rehab-depression|website=Billboard|accessdate=October 5, 2016}}</ref><ref name="xxl">{{cite web|last1=Madden|first1=Sidney|title=Kid Cudi Checks Into Rehab|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2016/10/kid-cudi-rehab/|website=XXL Mag|accessdate=October 5, 2016}}</ref><ref name="complex">{{cite web|last1=Setaro|first1=Shawn|title=Kid Cudi Checks Into Rehab for Depression, Shares Message for Fans|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2016/10/kid-cudi-rehab-depression|website=Complex|accessdate=October 5, 2016}}</ref>

===Family===
On March 26, 2010, Cudi's daughter, Vada Wamwene Mescudi, was born.<ref name="daughter">[https://twitter.com/wizardcud/status/162638922600554497 Photo: Ladies and gentleman, I think its time you all meet the #1 love in my life. The lil lady thats kept... [[Twitter]]]. twitter.com (January 12, 2012). Retrieved on January 26, 2012.</ref><ref name="bday">[https://twitter.com/wizardcud/status/162639923604750337 She'll be 2 March 26th....were gonna hit up a bar and celebrate [[Twitter]]]. Twitter.com (January 12, 2012). Retrieved on January 26, 2012.</ref> Throughout 2012, Cudi was in a quiet [[Child custody|custody]] battle over his daughter. Reports surfaced that Cudi gave up custody after his child's mother accused him of being an absentee father, as well as having violent tendencies and a "long history of consistent drug and alcohol abuse." These claims were disputed by Cudi and his attorney in a statement, which noted: "Cudi did not give up custody but reached an amicable agreement with the mother; that 'both parents are fit and proper persons to have custody of their child,' as stated in the final custody judgment; results came back negative for drugs in a drug test voluntarily taken by Cudi; and that the court acknowledged Cudi attempted to establish a relationship and visit his child since her birth and "voluntarily provided financial support, including child support, rent and other monthly payments, for his daughter since her birth until the time that a child support order was entered as part of the normal course of the case." Details of the official custody agreement remain private.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.complex.com/music/2012/11/kid-cudi-releases-statement-about-child-custody-battle | title = Kid Cudi's Attorney Responds to Child Custody Controversy | author = Andrew Martin | date = November 20, 2012 | accessdate = January 16, 2013 | publisher = Complex }}</ref> Cudi has since purchased a property in Chicago to be close to his daughter.<ref>{{cite news| url= http://www.3news.co.nz/Kid-Cudi-loses-custody-battle/tabid/418/articleID/277318/Default.aspx|work=3 News NZ | title= Kid Cudi loses custody battle| date=November 20, 2012}}</ref>

===Philanthropy===
On April 8, 2014, Didi Hirsch Mental Health Services announced that it would recognize mental health advocates Kid Cudi, [[Ronda Rousey]] and Natasha Tracy, during its annual Erasing the Stigma Leadership Awards on April 24, at the Beverly Hilton in Los Angeles. Committed to helping depressed and suicidal youth through the power of music, Cudi joined Didi Hirsch’s Erasing the Stigma Efforts as a Mental Health Ambassador.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.contactmusic.com/story/kid-cudi-honoured-for-work-with-mental-illness-charity_4170552 |title=Kid Cudi &#124; Kid Cudi Honoured For Work With Mental Illness Charity |publisher=Contactmusic.com |date=April 27, 2014 |accessdate=August 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/kid-cudi-ronda-rousey-natasha-174700028.html |title=Kid Cudi, Ronda Rousey and Natasha Tracy Take Center Stage at Didi Hirsch’s 18th Annual Erasing the Stigma Leadership Awards - Yahoo Finance |publisher=Finance.yahoo.com |date=April 8, 2014 |accessdate=August 9, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429061806/http://finance.yahoo.com/news/kid-cudi-ronda-rousey-natasha-174700028.html |archivedate=April 29, 2014 |df= }}</ref>

On February 7, 2015, Kid Cudi partnered with [[TED (conference)|TED]] to give a TED Talk at his former high school [[Shaker Heights High School|Shaker Heights]], to help inspire the students with his story, for the school's independently organized "TEDxSHHS" conference.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://shakerite.com/campus-and-city/2015/02/07/tedxshhs-awes-sold-out-audience/ | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150208170540/http://shakerite.com/campus-and-city/2015/02/07/tedxshhs-awes-sold-out-audience/ | dead-url = yes | archive-date = February 8, 2015 | title = TEDxSHHS Awes Sold-Out Audience | date = February 7, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.andralemarie.com/Home-Blog/2015/12/Kid-Cudi-Delivers-Empowering-Speech-In-a-TED-Talk-to-His-Former-High-School|title=Kid Cudi Delivers Empowering Speech In a TED Talk to His Former High School|last=|first=|date=December 28, 2015|website=http://www.andralemarie.com|access-date=June 5, 2017}}</ref>

Kid Cudi has also been a volunteer for Musicians on Call (MOC), a [[Charitable organization|charity]] with the mission of bringing live and recorded music to the bedsides of patients in healthcare facilities.<ref name="MOC">[http://www.musiciansoncall.org/site/News2?page=NewsArticle&id=5393&news_iv_ctrl=-1] {{dead link|date=December 2016}}</ref> In December 2015, Cudi arranged a [[dance party]] for the teenage participants of the [[Montefiore Medical Center|Children’s Hospital At Montefiore]]'s (CHAM) B-N-Fit program, in [[the Bronx]]. Kid Cudi also hosted a group of young patients and their families from CHAM, at his sold-out [[Roseland Ballroom]] shows in April 2016.<ref name="MOC"/>

In June 2016, 49 celebrities, including Kid Cudi, honored the 49 victims killed in the [[2016 Orlando nightclub shooting|Orlando shooting]] in a video tribute.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2016/06/49-celebrities-honor-49-people-killed-orlando-shooting-video |title=49 Celebrities Honor 49 People Killed in Orlando Shooting in Moving Video |publisher=Complex |date=June 29, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref>

===Relationships===
In 2009, Cudi began dating entertainment attorney<ref>[https://www.linkedin.com/in/jamiebaratta] {{dead link|date=December 2016}}</ref> Jamie Baratta. They were in an [[on-again, off-again relationship]], and were a prominent couple in the music industry.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.themoneytimes.com/node/117233 | title=Rapper Kid Cudi arrested for allegedly ripping woman's door off hinges | publisher= | work=TheMoneyTimes | date=June 12, 2010 | accessdate=March 18, 2013 | author=James, Natalie | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203000314/http://www.themoneytimes.com/node/117233 | archivedate=December 3, 2013 | df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.zimbio.com/photos/Kid+Cudi/Jamie+Baratta/Complex+Magazine+Music+Issue+Party+Kid+Cudi/-P9rkqFKlZi | title=Kid Cudi and Jamie Baratta»Photostream | publisher=[[Livingly Media]], Inc. | work=[[Zimbio]] | date=September 24, 2011| accessdate=March 18, 2013 | author=}}</ref> They ultimately broke up in 2012, but not before Cudi dedicated a song to her titled "[[Teleport 2 Me|Teleport 2 Me, Jamie]]", which he recorded as a member of the alternative rock duo, WZRD.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://rollingout.com/music/kid-cudi-goes-suicidal-for-provocative-new-complex-cover/ | title=KiD CuDi goes suicidal for provocative new ‘Complex’ cover | publisher=Steed Media Group, Inc. | work=Rolling Out | date=January 16, 2013| accessdate=March 18, 2013 | author=Robinson, Nicholas}}</ref>

