{{Portal|Anglicanism}}The [[Right Reverend]] '''Randolph Oswald George''' (died 18 July 2016) was the [[Anglican Diocese of Guyana|Bishop of Guyana]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anglicancommunion.org/tour/diocese.cfm?Idind=743|title=Page not found - Anglican Communion|first=Anglican Communion|last=Office|website=Anglican Communion Website}}</ref> from 1980<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stgeorges.org.gy/St%20Georges%20Cathedral%20Book.pdf|title=Diocesan history|publisher=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070709194741/http://www.stgeorges.org.gy/St%20Georges%20Cathedral%20Book.pdf|archivedate=2007-07-09|df=}}</ref> until 2009. Born in 1924 and educated at [[Codrington College|Codrington College, Barbados]], after a curacy at ''St Peter [[Barbados]]'' he spent a decade in [[England]]. Successively he was [[Curate]] at [[Leigh, Surrey|Leigh]], [[Ardwick]] and [[Lavender Hill]]<ref>[[Crockford's clerical directory]]1976 Lambeth, Church House {{ISBN|0-19-200008-X}}</ref>  before returning to become [[Chaplain]] to the [[William James Hughes|Bishop of Trinidad]]. From there he became [[Rector (ecclesiastical)|Rector]] of [[Couva]] then ''All Saints, [[Port of Spain]]'' before being elected to the [[Deanery]] of the [[Anglican Diocese of Guyana]] in 1971. Promoted to be the [[Suffragan Bishop]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.landofsixpeoples.com/news301/nc3041316.htm|title=Put Guyana first, foster respect, accept differences|website=www.landofsixpeoples.com}}</ref> of ''Stabroek''<ref>The name by which [[Guyana]] was known until 1822 [[Encyclopædia Britannica]] 1955 edn Vol 10 p 955</ref> in 1976, four years later he became [[Bishop]] -a position he held until 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stabroeknews.com/2008/letters/12/30/bishop-george-will-be-remembered-for-touching-the-lives-of-members-of-his-congregation-in-positive-ways/|title=Bishop George will be remembered for touching the lives of members of his congregation in positive ways – Stabroek News|first=Staff|last=Writer|date=30 December 2008|publisher=}}</ref>

George died on 18 July 2016 at the age of 92.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stalbans.anglican.org/rt-revd-randolph-george-rip/|title=The Rt Revd Randolph George, RIP - Diocese of St Albans|date=19 July 2016|publisher=}}</ref>

